    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "With the spir-its of the right--eous that have been per-fect--ed, do Thou grant rest, O Sav-iour, to the souls of Thy ser--vants, pre-serv-ing__ them for the bless-ed life with Thee, O Friend of man.\n\nIn the place__ of Thy rest, O Lord, where all Thy Saints re-pose, grant rest al--so to the souls__ of Thy ser--vants, for Thou a-lone__ art im-mor--tal.\n\nGlo-ry to the Fa-ther, and to the Son, and to the Ho-ly Spir--it.\n\nThou__ art our God, Who didst de-scend in-to Ha--des and didst dis-pel the pangs__ of them that were in fet--ters; do Thou Thy-self grant rest, O Sav--iour, to the souls__ of Thy ser--vants.\n\nBoth now and ev--er, and un-to the ag--es of ag-es. A-men.\n\nO_ thou__ on-ly pure and un-de-filed__ Vir--gin, who with-out seed didst con-ceive God in thy womb, pray thou that the souls__ of thy ser-vants may be saved._____"
    }
  }
